President Donald Trump has issued a proclamation declaring January 2020 as National Slavery and Human Trafficking Prevention Month. The proclamation emphasizes the seriousness of human trafficking and its impact on individuals and communities worldwide. It highlights the need for a comprehensive framework to combat human trafficking, including prevention programs, victim protections, and expanded criminal statutes. The proclamation also acknowledges the efforts of various government agencies, such as the Department of Justice, Department of Homeland Security, and Department of State, in combating human trafficking. President Trump calls upon all Americans to recognize their role in ending human trafficking and to observe the month with appropriate programs and activities aimed at prevention and awareness.